title: Type5-Q1
prompt_html: In a poll, a 90% confidence interval for the proportion of voters supporting Finn is (0.46, 0.50). For Pablo, the 90% confidence interval is (0.49, 0.53). What can we conclude?

choices.label: A
choices.html: Since the intervals overlap, neither candidate is clearly ahead.

choices.label: B
choices.html: Since Pablo’s lowest is greater than Finn’s highest, Pablo is ahead.

choices.label: C
choices.html: Since Finn’s lowest is greater than Pablo’s highest, Finn is ahead.

choices.label: D
choices.html: Both are tied exactly.

choices.label: E
choices.html: There is no way to tell.
